President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Seminole Tribe of Florida and ordered Federal aid to supplement their efforts in areas affected by Hurricane Irma. Federal funding is now available for affected individuals of the Tribe, which can include grants for temporary housing, home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to help with recovery. Funding is also available for emergency work and facility repairs on a cost-sharing basis. Assistance for emergency protective measures is authorized at 100% of eligible costs for 30 days, and funding for hazard mitigation measures is available on a cost-sharing basis. Willie G. Nunn has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance online or by phone. For further information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted.